⬇️Dos and Don’ts: wide legs pants & shoes ⬇️
Since there is a lot of fabric on the lower part of your outfit, you want to consider “lighter” options for your shoes to have a good balance.

Sneakers: Leave the chunky options for a different outfit as they will make your outfit appear bottom heavy, the fabric will bunch where the shoes begin make the outfit look messy. Instead opt for a pair of sneakers with the low platform or a high top is a good option.

Boots: Rewear your favorite ankle boots as the pants will hide the  awkward height of the boots that is usually unflattering. Choose pointy toe as they will make your outfit look elegant, classy & make you appear taller as well. 

Flats: pointy toe or almond shape are better choices compared to square or round styles. If choosing heels, be aware where the fabric ends: mid heel or completely covering it are the best options.
